WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:40.400


00:00:58.513 --> 00:01:02.748
[In-season Angry Snapper]
- Yes! It's an angry snapper! - Angry!

00:01:11.097 --> 00:01:12.815
What?

00:01:14.097 --> 00:01:18.888
Man, another bust today.

00:01:19.584 --> 00:01:23.547
Meet another cell who's half-unemployed now.

00:01:23.547 --> 00:01:25.556
Fishing Cell.

00:01:35.305 --> 00:01:39.195
894 days of going home with nothing.

00:01:47.597 --> 00:01:48.822
And then...

00:01:48.822 --> 00:01:51.647
Then came day 895.

00:01:58.888 --> 00:02:01.835
- Angry!
- I caught one!

00:02:01.835 --> 00:02:04.720
At last, he hooked one.

00:02:05.555 --> 00:02:06.805
- An angry snapper!
- Angry!

00:02:06.805 --> 00:02:09.180
- It's the angry snapper!
- Angry snapper.

00:02:09.180 --> 00:02:12.888
It's a rare fish only caught
when Yumi gets mad.

00:02:12.888 --> 00:02:16.566
The angry snapper
came back from near extinction...

00:02:21.772 --> 00:02:24.055
It's an angry snapper!

00:02:24.055 --> 00:02:26.055
right when PD Shin forgot all his manners.

00:02:26.055 --> 00:02:27.097
Angry!

00:02:27.097 --> 00:02:30.530
I came for those too.

00:02:30.530 --> 00:02:32.407
That was the last batch.

00:02:32.407 --> 00:02:34.555
They sell out fast.

00:02:34.555 --> 00:02:36.972
Right. So...

00:02:36.972 --> 00:02:38.305
Anyway, I'll get going.

00:02:38.305 --> 00:02:40.397
See you next week.

00:02:44.101 --> 00:02:46.180
- Score, another angry snapper!
- Angry!

00:02:46.180 --> 00:02:49.548
When PD Shin grabbed them all for himself.

00:02:49.548 --> 00:02:52.476
But Maltese aren't that smart.

00:02:53.302 --> 00:02:54.637
Angry!

00:02:54.637 --> 00:02:56.681
Don't all dogs do that?

00:02:56.681 --> 00:02:58.980
Unless it's a lizard.

00:03:01.310 --> 00:03:04.438
Angry!

00:03:04.438 --> 00:03:07.605
Maltese... Don't they eat poop?

00:03:10.513 --> 00:03:11.922
[PD Shin]

00:03:16.013 --> 00:03:19.522
Angry!

00:03:23.805 --> 00:03:26.460
- Angry!
- Angry!

00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:28.337
It's a full catch!

00:03:28.337 --> 00:03:33.225
Yumi's absolutely furious!

00:03:37.179 --> 00:03:39.847
Hey, Lullaby Cell, get up.

00:03:39.847 --> 00:03:41.263
What is it?

00:03:41.263 --> 00:03:43.352
Help Yumi fall asleep.

00:03:43.352 --> 00:03:46.147
It's after two in the morning
and she won't sleep.

00:03:46.147 --> 00:03:48.022
What?

00:03:58.930 --> 00:04:03.555
Seriously, the more I think about it,
the crazier it gets.

00:04:05.458 --> 00:04:09.805
♪ Go to sleep, go to sleep, sweet Yumi ♪

00:04:09.805 --> 00:04:12.173
Since Yumi's too furious to sleep,

00:04:12.173 --> 00:04:13.847
- I'm stuck on the clock too.
- Sleep well.

00:04:13.847 --> 00:04:16.135
My stomach's empty.

00:04:16.135 --> 00:04:19.388
Hey, look at the clock. You're hungry again?

00:04:19.388 --> 00:04:22.097
I want fried dumplings.

00:04:22.097 --> 00:04:25.097
Fried dumplings!

00:04:25.097 --> 00:04:28.855
Hungry Cell wants a midnight snack for once.

00:04:34.430 --> 00:04:39.730
I'm so ticked off I can't sleep.
That Shin Soon Rok.

00:04:44.097 --> 00:04:45.998
Hey, Coco.

00:04:45.998 --> 00:04:47.666
You can't sleep either?

00:04:47.666 --> 00:04:49.794
You're all worked up too, aren't you?

00:04:49.794 --> 00:04:52.513
It was just humiliating.

00:04:52.513 --> 00:04:54.006
I'm so sorry, Coco.

00:04:54.006 --> 00:04:55.680
Poor thing.

00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:58.302
Sorry I let him say that to you.

00:04:58.302 --> 00:05:01.555
That was humiliating, wasn't it?

00:05:01.555 --> 00:05:03.974
I bet that guy's actually a sociopath.

00:05:03.974 --> 00:05:07.611
Who's that heartless to an animal?

00:05:08.222 --> 00:05:11.315
Sociopath? Or personality disorder?

00:05:11.315 --> 00:05:14.151
Or maybe both?

00:05:14.151 --> 00:05:16.105
Definitely both.

00:05:19.763 --> 00:05:23.805
So how do sociopaths
and personality disorders connect?

00:05:23.805 --> 00:05:27.388
I bet there are tons of personality disorders.

00:05:27.388 --> 00:05:29.772
Let me dig into this.

00:05:39.430 --> 00:05:41.055
Oh hey, Bulletin Board Cell.

00:05:41.055 --> 00:05:43.013
You're still awake?

00:05:43.013 --> 00:05:45.097
I got slammed with new notes.

00:05:45.097 --> 00:05:46.680
Can't remember the last time.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.055
[Talking trash about a Maltese?!]

00:05:48.055 --> 00:05:49.555
[Replace him, Shin Soon Rok]
[How should we get revenge?]

00:05:49.555 --> 00:05:51.377
"Replace him, Shin Soon Rok."

00:05:51.377 --> 00:05:54.305
"What a jerk. How do I get back at him?"

00:05:54.305 --> 00:05:58.146
"He insulted a Maltese?
I'll never forgive him."

00:06:02.972 --> 00:06:06.013
Oh no, what now?

00:06:06.013 --> 00:06:07.638
You need to look after her.

00:06:07.638 --> 00:06:09.180
Coco's stressed out because of this.

00:06:09.180 --> 00:06:11.805
Look, her coat's gone all dull!

00:06:14.097 --> 00:06:15.305
Don't let it get you down.

00:06:15.305 --> 00:06:17.105
You okay?

00:06:20.888 --> 00:06:23.471
Wait, there's no bungeoppang left.

00:06:23.471 --> 00:06:28.222
Is he kidding? He took all eight for himself?

00:06:28.222 --> 00:06:31.938
You're kidding, there's none left?

00:06:32.895 --> 00:06:35.222
After the fried dumplings,
it was bungeoppang's turn.

00:06:35.222 --> 00:06:37.430
I have to have it, right now!

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:42.688
I'm craving
Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang!

00:06:44.532 --> 00:06:46.993
Bungeoppang!

00:06:46.993 --> 00:06:49.597
Bungeoppang!

00:06:49.597 --> 00:06:50.888
Hey, you guys!

00:06:50.888 --> 00:06:52.930
What's with all this racket
in the middle of the night?

00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:56.972
- I have to sleep now to write tomorrow.
- My bungeoppang!

00:06:56.972 --> 00:07:00.772
It'd been a while
since the town stayed up all night.

00:07:35.597 --> 00:07:37.480
Ready to go?

00:07:45.722 --> 00:07:47.595
Man, I'm so tired.

00:07:47.595 --> 00:07:50.772
Lost so much sleep because of that jerk.

00:07:51.805 --> 00:07:53.513
Coco.

00:07:53.513 --> 00:07:55.227
Your mom's coming today.

00:07:55.227 --> 00:07:57.313
She said she's coming to pick you up.

00:07:57.313 --> 00:07:59.647
Lucky you, Coco.

00:08:18.430 --> 00:08:20.211
- Isn't that PD Shin?
- What?

00:08:20.211 --> 00:08:22.555
Seriously, why do I keep seeing him?

00:08:22.555 --> 00:08:26.438
The bungeoppang place is that way.

00:08:27.240 --> 00:08:30.638
Don't tell me he's buying bungeoppang already?

00:08:30.638 --> 00:08:33.022
Like I'm letting that happen.

00:08:34.763 --> 00:08:38.138
Hold on, Yumi's wearing those raggedy sweats!

00:08:38.138 --> 00:08:40.624
And Yumi didn't even wash up!

00:08:48.322 --> 00:08:51.813
Like that even matters right now?

00:09:13.263 --> 00:09:14.555
Excuse me, sir!

00:09:14.555 --> 00:09:15.557
Hello.

00:09:15.557 --> 00:09:16.680
- Hello.
- Hi.

00:09:16.680 --> 00:09:19.436
Give me every Strawberry Cream
Custard Bungeoppang here.

00:09:19.436 --> 00:09:21.479
- Every single one?
- Yes, please.

00:09:21.479 --> 00:09:22.647
Every last one.

00:09:22.647 --> 00:09:24.427
Oh, is it a group order?

00:09:24.427 --> 00:09:26.180
How many per box, then?

00:09:26.180 --> 00:09:28.862
Skip the boxes. I'll take whatever's here.

00:09:28.862 --> 00:09:32.449
One second, let me count them up.

00:09:32.449 --> 00:09:34.242
No, just give them all to me.

00:09:34.242 --> 00:09:35.805
Just all of them. Every single one.

00:09:35.805 --> 00:09:37.847
- That's more than 40.
- More is better!

00:09:37.847 --> 00:09:40.063
- Okay.
- Thank you.

00:09:43.123 --> 00:09:44.763
Could you hurry a little, please?

00:09:44.763 --> 00:09:46.472
- Okay.
- I'm running late for work.

00:09:46.472 --> 00:09:49.638
- Oh, are you sharing at the office?
- No.

00:09:49.638 --> 00:09:51.924
I'm eating every last one myself.

00:09:51.924 --> 00:09:54.230
Oh, okay...

00:09:59.172 --> 00:10:01.847
Oh, hi, PD Shin!

00:10:01.847 --> 00:10:02.847
Hi, Writer Kim.

00:10:02.847 --> 00:10:04.606
[Bbang-eo Bbang-eo]

00:10:04.606 --> 00:10:07.233
What a coincidence seeing you here again!

00:10:07.233 --> 00:10:08.430
Yeah, small world.

00:10:08.430 --> 00:10:10.972
You're really into bungeoppang, huh?

00:10:10.972 --> 00:10:12.989
Strawberry Cream Custard ones again?

00:10:12.989 --> 00:10:14.449
Yeah.

00:10:14.449 --> 00:10:16.201
Wait, seriously?

00:10:16.201 --> 00:10:18.620
You might be out of luck.

00:10:18.620 --> 00:10:19.972
All set.

00:10:19.972 --> 00:10:22.855
Thanks so much!

00:10:26.972 --> 00:10:29.320
Thank you.

00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:32.055
All right, done.

00:10:32.055 --> 00:10:34.305
- So all of those are...
- Yes.

00:10:34.305 --> 00:10:36.513
These are all

00:10:36.513 --> 00:10:39.397
Strawberry Cream Custard.

00:10:40.274 --> 00:10:42.522
Catch you next week!

00:10:46.064 --> 00:10:48.511
Writer Kim...

00:10:48.511 --> 00:10:50.438
The bungeoppang...

00:10:55.513 --> 00:10:57.597
Hello.

00:10:58.847 --> 00:11:00.829
Oh, hello.

00:11:00.829 --> 00:11:04.598
If you came for the Strawberry Cream Custard,
sorry, but we're sold out.

00:11:04.598 --> 00:11:08.097
I have to make more filling,
so they won't be ready till the afternoon.

00:11:28.638 --> 00:11:30.438
Right then...

00:11:39.347 --> 00:11:41.480
[Endorphin]

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:45.813
It'd been a while since Endorphin showed up.

00:11:54.222 --> 00:11:56.597
Coco, did you see that? Did you?

00:11:56.597 --> 00:11:59.180
That stunned look on his face.

00:11:59.180 --> 00:12:01.638
I got payback for you, Coco.

00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:03.647
Pretty good, right?

00:12:08.388 --> 00:12:10.647
Oh, that felt so good.

00:12:15.055 --> 00:12:17.763
♪ Pissed off? Eat some angry snapper ♪

00:12:17.763 --> 00:12:20.222
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

00:12:20.222 --> 00:12:22.638
♪ Fired up? Cook some angry snapper ♪

00:12:22.638 --> 00:12:25.180
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

00:12:25.180 --> 00:12:27.347
All you Cells who love Yumi!

00:12:27.347 --> 00:12:30.022
Make a circle over your heads!

00:12:32.555 --> 00:12:34.763
One, two, three, four!

00:12:34.763 --> 00:12:37.930
♪ Let's eat, let's eat, let's eat ♪

00:12:37.930 --> 00:12:43.522
♪ Dig into that angry snapper ♪

00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:48.688
It was party time again after forever.

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:56.568
What a nice breeze.

00:12:56.568 --> 00:12:59.647
Beautiful day, isn't it, Coco?

00:13:06.202 --> 00:13:09.055
Who cares how smart a Maltese is?

00:13:09.055 --> 00:13:11.305
That's not what my writing's about.

00:13:11.305 --> 00:13:13.668
Would a poodle change the whole theme?

00:13:13.668 --> 00:13:15.764
Does it change the male lead at all?

00:13:15.764 --> 00:13:18.388
Coco, what's got her so mad?

00:13:18.388 --> 00:13:20.638
And then guess what he said?

00:13:20.638 --> 00:13:22.635
He said Maltese eat poop too.

00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:26.138
Is he out of his mind or what?

00:13:26.138 --> 00:13:27.156
Eating poop?

00:13:27.156 --> 00:13:29.847
Yeah! He said Maltese eat poop.

00:13:29.847 --> 00:13:32.472
As a Maltese owner, isn't that ridiculous?

00:13:32.472 --> 00:13:34.314
That's straight-up disrespect.

00:13:34.314 --> 00:13:36.563
Disrespect to all of us owners.

00:13:38.152 --> 00:13:41.763
Though Coco eats poop, so I can't fight it.

00:13:41.763 --> 00:13:42.880
Wait, what?

00:13:42.880 --> 00:13:46.409
She licks her own poop sometimes.

00:13:46.409 --> 00:13:49.763
No big deal, just brush her teeth.

00:13:49.763 --> 00:13:52.063
Isn't that right, Coco?

00:13:55.513 --> 00:13:57.472
Hey, by the way,

00:13:57.472 --> 00:13:59.098
why do you look so happy?

00:13:59.098 --> 00:14:00.805
Me? Happy?

00:14:00.805 --> 00:14:04.147
You totally are. It's been a while.

00:14:04.805 --> 00:14:08.436
No, I'm really not cheerful.

00:14:08.436 --> 00:14:10.730
I'm just mad.

00:14:12.722 --> 00:14:15.605
Why? You're mad too, right?

00:14:16.430 --> 00:14:18.263
Oh, right.

00:14:26.366 --> 00:14:27.472
Here, take it.

00:14:27.472 --> 00:14:29.347
Huh? Is this Bungeoppang?

00:14:29.347 --> 00:14:31.055
I never confront people directly.

00:14:31.055 --> 00:14:33.623
I take revenge gracefully.

00:14:33.623 --> 00:14:37.772
That's pro Writer Kim's way with amateurs.

00:14:39.118 --> 00:14:41.972
Gracefully, yeah.

00:14:41.972 --> 00:14:45.888
Bye Coco, let's hang out again, okay?

00:14:45.888 --> 00:14:48.722
Thanks so much!
I'll treat you to a meal next week.

00:14:48.722 --> 00:14:50.765
Alright, off you go.

00:14:50.765 --> 00:14:52.763
- Bye.
- Say bye-bye. That's a good girl.

00:14:52.763 --> 00:14:55.313
- Bye now.
- Bye.

00:15:02.888 --> 00:15:05.763
[Take care of yourself. See you next time]

00:15:05.763 --> 00:15:08.138
- Have a safe trip home.
- Have a safe trip home.

00:15:08.138 --> 00:15:10.116
- Now the Maltese is leaving too.
- Bye-bye.

00:15:10.116 --> 00:15:11.930
Once the angry snapper festival ended,

00:15:11.930 --> 00:15:14.855
the village felt empty all over again.

00:15:15.956 --> 00:15:18.263
Finally, I can get some work done.

00:15:18.263 --> 00:15:20.168
Haven't gotten a word down since yesterday.

00:15:20.168 --> 00:15:22.522
It's all Shin Soon Rok's fault.

00:15:44.985 --> 00:15:48.230
- Yes, who's there?
- It's a delivery.

00:15:49.781 --> 00:15:52.105
I didn't order anything.

00:15:56.913 --> 00:15:58.897
What is this?

00:16:04.596 --> 00:16:07.299
[To Writer Kim, From Shin Soon Rok]

00:16:07.299 --> 00:16:09.355
From Shin Soon Rok?

00:16:10.677 --> 00:16:13.013
Shin Soon Rok?

00:16:13.013 --> 00:16:14.980
What's he up to now?

00:16:21.513 --> 00:16:24.691
Soiel Bakery?

00:16:24.691 --> 00:16:27.110
No way!

00:16:27.110 --> 00:16:29.555
It's Soiel Bakery!

00:16:29.555 --> 00:16:34.097
The chef worked at a top 3-star Michelin spot,

00:16:34.097 --> 00:16:36.388
famous for seasonal course desserts!

00:16:36.388 --> 00:16:38.830
A bakery that's all about desserts!

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:42.388
Money won't even get you a table there!

00:16:42.388 --> 00:16:44.347
PD Shin actually sent that?

00:16:44.347 --> 00:16:47.397
PD Shin, who wouldn't even share
a single bungeoppang?

00:17:11.279 --> 00:17:13.563
Oh, these look so cute!

00:17:18.138 --> 00:17:20.038
These are so adorable!

00:17:20.038 --> 00:17:21.131
Wait a second.

00:17:21.131 --> 00:17:23.975
This isn't something
you can get delivered online.

00:17:23.975 --> 00:17:26.711
He went there himself to buy and send these.

00:17:26.711 --> 00:17:28.180
Bottom line,

00:17:28.180 --> 00:17:29.715
this is heartfelt.

00:17:29.715 --> 00:17:31.097
What's this about?

00:17:32.013 --> 00:17:34.135
That spooked him earlier.

00:17:34.135 --> 00:17:37.188
He realized he slipped up.

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:44.972
Seeing me buy out
all the bungeoppang scared him.

00:17:44.972 --> 00:17:48.438
Gosh, he's so pathetic it's actually endearing.

00:17:50.026 --> 00:17:53.522
These must be amazing.

00:17:54.722 --> 00:17:57.355
These are too pretty to eat, honestly.

00:18:02.263 --> 00:18:06.252
Maybe shoot him a thank-you message first.

00:18:06.252 --> 00:18:07.930
Right, good thinking.

00:18:07.930 --> 00:18:10.222
He's not a terrible person or anything.

00:18:10.222 --> 00:18:12.632
He was just immature, that's all.

00:18:12.632 --> 00:18:14.397
Right.

00:18:24.888 --> 00:18:27.180
Who is it this late?

00:18:30.430 --> 00:18:32.480
Who's there?

00:18:33.347 --> 00:18:37.013
Writer Kim, it's me, PD Shin.

00:18:37.013 --> 00:18:38.549
Excuse me?

00:18:38.549 --> 00:18:40.222
Why is he here?

00:18:40.222 --> 00:18:41.763
Did he come to say sorry?

00:18:41.763 --> 00:18:43.805
He sent food and now he's showing up in person?

00:18:48.333 --> 00:18:49.835
Oh, PD Shin.

00:18:49.835 --> 00:18:53.138
Sorry for showing up so late.

00:18:53.138 --> 00:18:54.589
It's fine.

00:18:54.589 --> 00:18:57.897
But what brings you here at this hour?

00:18:58.552 --> 00:19:00.855
- Were you maybe...
- I was just thinking about...

00:19:03.015 --> 00:19:04.808
Sorry?

00:19:04.808 --> 00:19:07.644
The dessert I sent...

00:19:07.644 --> 00:19:09.263
Oh yeah, I got them.

00:19:09.263 --> 00:19:11.597
I was literally just about to message you.

00:19:11.597 --> 00:19:15.605
- Oh, they look so delicious...
- Oh, you already tried them.

00:19:16.862 --> 00:19:18.522
What?

00:19:19.740 --> 00:19:21.855
Got it.

00:19:23.618 --> 00:19:24.680
Hold on.

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:26.305
This feels weird again.

00:19:26.305 --> 00:19:28.540
Something's not right again, is it?

00:19:28.540 --> 00:19:31.752
Oh wait, I think I get it now.

00:19:31.752 --> 00:19:34.046
Wait,

00:19:34.046 --> 00:19:36.590
did you send this by mistake?

00:19:36.590 --> 00:19:39.772
Was it meant for another Writer Kim...

00:19:41.386 --> 00:19:43.063
Yeah.

00:19:45.474 --> 00:19:46.641
Angry!

00:19:46.641 --> 00:19:47.972
Angry! Angry!

00:19:47.972 --> 00:19:48.972
Angry!

00:19:48.972 --> 00:19:51.805
- Well now, it's prime time for Angry Snapper.
- Angry!

00:19:51.805 --> 00:19:53.472
Angry!

00:19:53.472 --> 00:19:55.730
Angry!

00:19:58.805 --> 00:20:00.771
[Episode 5: A Delivery from PD Shin]

00:20:01.930 --> 00:20:04.563
There's something called a compliment delivery.

00:20:06.870 --> 00:20:08.938
Delivery!

00:20:11.763 --> 00:20:13.888
No way, it's a compliment delivery!

00:20:13.888 --> 00:20:18.430
Every praise is delivered directly
to the specific cell it's meant for.

00:20:18.430 --> 00:20:20.972
These delivery boxes contain a soul...

00:20:20.972 --> 00:20:23.720
Hi! I'm here to give you something.

00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:25.388
No way, it's a present!

00:20:25.388 --> 00:20:26.972
This is so exciting!

00:20:26.972 --> 00:20:30.605
Which then presents a gift to the cell.

00:20:31.847 --> 00:20:33.180
Sir.

00:20:33.180 --> 00:20:35.982
Here's everything you asked for yesterday.

00:20:35.982 --> 00:20:38.647
Oh, thanks. Right.

00:20:39.472 --> 00:20:42.938
Man, you never miss a thing.

00:20:46.596 --> 00:20:48.930
Compliment delivery for Rational Cell!

00:20:48.930 --> 00:20:50.888
No way!

00:20:50.888 --> 00:20:52.597
- It's a compliment delivery!
- Here you go.

00:20:52.597 --> 00:20:54.513
- Thanks a lot!
- Back in my rookie days,

00:20:54.513 --> 00:20:58.813
- Awesome. Time to ask for more focus.
- a single compliment delivery really lifted me.

00:21:00.132 --> 00:21:01.972
Hello, Writer Kim.

00:21:01.972 --> 00:21:04.347
Hey, you're here.

00:21:04.347 --> 00:21:07.647
One thing's different now
after all these years.

00:21:11.263 --> 00:21:13.972
I didn't have quite enough time,

00:21:13.972 --> 00:21:17.438
so it's not super detailed yet.

00:21:19.138 --> 00:21:21.323
Alright, ship it off to Na Hui.

00:21:22.722 --> 00:21:24.055
It's that Yumi has become

00:21:24.055 --> 00:21:27.480
a person who praises others now.

00:21:28.222 --> 00:21:29.597
Good job.

00:21:29.597 --> 00:21:30.680
Seriously?

00:21:30.680 --> 00:21:33.180
Yeah, this is good.

00:21:33.180 --> 00:21:35.013
It's gotten so much better.

00:21:35.013 --> 00:21:36.597
Thanks for all the hard work.

00:21:36.597 --> 00:21:38.644
I was bracing to get chewed out.

00:21:38.644 --> 00:21:40.938
Thanks so much.

00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:46.680
But it feels really light.

00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.472
Isn't this a little half-hearted?

00:21:48.472 --> 00:21:50.972
You can't mean it every single time.

00:21:50.972 --> 00:21:53.563
She's been kind of discouraged lately.

00:21:54.430 --> 00:21:57.680
Sure, I'll see you tomorrow.

00:21:57.680 --> 00:22:00.680
She actually praised me.

00:22:01.638 --> 00:22:04.378
[It's just a brief idea,
but I'm suggesting it for your review]

00:22:07.972 --> 00:22:10.522
Why is she not improving at all?

00:22:15.805 --> 00:22:18.780
Sometimes even hollow praise is necessary,

00:22:18.780 --> 00:22:21.647
she figured that out with age.

00:22:25.680 --> 00:22:27.097
But...

00:22:27.097 --> 00:22:28.815
[Maltese wins dog show]

00:22:32.763 --> 00:22:34.097
Shin Soon Rok...

00:22:34.097 --> 00:22:37.347
I know exactly what kind of guy you are.

00:22:37.347 --> 00:22:40.063
[Winner at the dog show, too!]
Bet he opens the meeting with Maltese talk.

00:22:40.063 --> 00:22:41.523
Alright then.

00:22:41.523 --> 00:22:43.108
That dog show story was made up.

00:22:43.108 --> 00:22:45.819
It was a complete fib,

00:22:45.819 --> 00:22:47.863
but I'll find something similar

00:22:47.863 --> 00:22:50.039
and send over the link, no matter what.

00:22:50.657 --> 00:22:52.367
I mean, with so many competitions out there,

00:22:52.367 --> 00:22:54.961
there's got to be a Maltese runner-up.

00:22:56.013 --> 00:22:57.675
[Most wins at the dog show!]

00:23:01.638 --> 00:23:02.960
Oh, hey Na Hui.

00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:06.340
Did you read PD Shin's email?

00:23:06.340 --> 00:23:08.180
Email? No.

00:23:08.180 --> 00:23:11.638
He reached out and mentioned
he sent the script feedback two nights ago.

00:23:11.638 --> 00:23:13.722
He noticed you haven't seen it yet

00:23:13.722 --> 00:23:17.191
and asked if you could
check it before the meeting.

00:23:18.050 --> 00:23:19.728
There's more feedback?

00:23:19.728 --> 00:23:21.980
He's still not done with the Maltese thing?

00:23:21.980 --> 00:23:25.484
Did PD Shin fight a Maltese
in his past life or what?

00:23:25.484 --> 00:23:28.445
I don't really know what it says either.

00:23:28.445 --> 00:23:30.305
Got it, I'll take a look.

00:23:30.305 --> 00:23:32.180
Okay.

00:23:33.116 --> 00:23:35.501
Seriously.

00:23:38.745 --> 00:23:39.763
[Maltese wins dog show]

00:23:39.763 --> 00:23:42.209
[Shin Soon Rok]

00:23:42.209 --> 00:23:44.903
Writer Kim, it's Shin Soon Rok.

00:23:44.903 --> 00:23:47.422
Here's some more feedback for you.

00:23:47.422 --> 00:23:48.465
[Sent at 02:12]
Seriously?

00:23:48.465 --> 00:23:50.850
Two in the morning?

00:23:51.597 --> 00:23:54.179
So the Maltese is absolutely off the table?

00:23:54.179 --> 00:23:57.222
Important enough to email
at two in the morning?

00:23:57.222 --> 00:24:00.305
I've had it with you, Shin Soon Rok.

00:24:03.814 --> 00:24:06.138
And why is it this long?

00:24:06.138 --> 00:24:10.180
He barely talks but writes forever.

00:24:13.805 --> 00:24:16.576
The thing that caught my eye in this draft

00:24:16.576 --> 00:24:20.013
was the way the emotions change.

00:24:20.013 --> 00:24:21.039
Like,

00:24:21.039 --> 00:24:23.055
"How could someone

00:24:23.055 --> 00:24:26.263
- in love be so calm?"
- He gets it.

00:24:26.920 --> 00:24:28.130
He really gets it.

00:24:28.130 --> 00:24:31.388
He gets exactly what I was going for.

00:24:32.048 --> 00:24:34.551
I've been waiting for notes like this.

00:24:34.551 --> 00:24:36.852
Yes, exactly!

00:24:37.512 --> 00:24:39.389
What?

00:24:39.389 --> 00:24:43.226
Since when is he this insightful?

00:24:43.226 --> 00:24:45.603
I'm kind of thrown.

00:24:45.603 --> 00:24:49.198
I think it'll land as a big turn.

00:24:50.066 --> 00:24:52.694
The emotional void in this scene

00:24:52.694 --> 00:24:54.696
does more than just explain what's happening.

00:24:54.696 --> 00:24:59.959
It makes you reconsider when to end things.

00:25:07.834 --> 00:25:10.722
This one's the real deal!

00:25:10.722 --> 00:25:14.730
Finally, a compliment delivery from the heart!

00:25:15.592 --> 00:25:18.602
- Deliver this to PD Shin.
- Got it.

00:25:20.347 --> 00:25:23.022
This kind deserves a reply.

00:25:31.357 --> 00:25:35.320
Hi PD Shin, I just read your email.

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:38.323
The feedback's really going to help.

00:25:38.323 --> 00:25:39.805
The part I was stuck on is...

00:25:39.805 --> 00:25:42.180
Hey, where're you going?

00:25:43.222 --> 00:25:44.888
You...

00:25:50.597 --> 00:25:54.631
[Pride Cell]

00:25:54.631 --> 00:25:57.258
When did you wake up?

00:25:57.258 --> 00:25:59.347
- Give me that!
- Hey, what's your problem?

00:25:59.347 --> 00:26:01.679
No compliments for Shin Soon Rok.

00:26:01.679 --> 00:26:05.107
I, Pride Cell, won't allow it!

00:26:08.436 --> 00:26:11.147
This is heavy.

00:26:11.147 --> 00:26:13.358
Compliment deliveries for Shin Soon Rok

00:26:13.358 --> 00:26:17.022
are suspended for now, understand?

00:26:18.988 --> 00:26:21.282
Forget it.

00:26:21.282 --> 00:26:24.035
[PD Shin]
He did one thing right

00:26:24.035 --> 00:26:26.253
and I'm overreacting.

00:26:26.996 --> 00:26:28.498
PD Shin,

00:26:28.498 --> 00:26:31.258
I've read your email.

00:26:34.254 --> 00:26:36.764
A compliment would be wasted on you.

00:26:45.388 --> 00:26:47.586
[PD Shin]

00:26:49.644 --> 00:26:51.437
Hey, PD Shin.

00:26:51.437 --> 00:26:53.231
Hello.

00:26:53.231 --> 00:26:55.066
Writer Kim,

00:26:55.066 --> 00:26:56.693
you're not at the studio?

00:26:56.693 --> 00:26:59.112
I just stepped out.

00:26:59.112 --> 00:27:00.530
What's up?

00:27:00.530 --> 00:27:02.073
Well...

00:27:02.073 --> 00:27:04.575
I came by to give you something.

00:27:04.575 --> 00:27:06.411
Then...

00:27:06.411 --> 00:27:08.496
I'll leave it with security.

00:27:08.496 --> 00:27:12.049
Wait, I'm down at the parking lot.

00:27:26.973 --> 00:27:28.433
Oh, PD Shin.

00:27:28.433 --> 00:27:30.192
Hello.

00:27:31.185 --> 00:27:33.747
What brings you here unannounced?

00:27:35.189 --> 00:27:37.692
Just wanted to drop this off.

00:27:37.692 --> 00:27:39.986
What is it?

00:27:39.986 --> 00:27:42.322
This is the same dessert as yesterday.

00:27:42.322 --> 00:27:43.448
Oh my.

00:27:43.448 --> 00:27:45.116
I'm sorry about yesterday.

00:27:45.116 --> 00:27:48.870
Writer Kim Ju Ho specifically asked for it.

00:27:48.870 --> 00:27:52.381
Oh, these things happen.

00:27:53.207 --> 00:27:55.717
You didn't have to...

00:27:56.763 --> 00:27:59.297
Yes, dessert!

00:27:59.297 --> 00:28:02.306
Yes, dessert!

00:28:02.306 --> 00:28:06.055
Three Michelin-star dessert!

00:28:06.055 --> 00:28:09.849
I've wanted this so bad!

00:28:09.849 --> 00:28:12.352
Smooth move, PD Shin.

00:28:12.352 --> 00:28:13.936
Deliver this to PD Shin.

00:28:13.936 --> 00:28:16.707
Put my whole heart into it.

00:28:17.513 --> 00:28:19.347
Okay, I got it.

00:28:25.222 --> 00:28:28.680
What?

00:28:28.680 --> 00:28:31.913
Hey! Where are you going now?

00:28:31.913 --> 00:28:34.707
Hungry Cell really wants this sent.

00:28:34.707 --> 00:28:35.847
I, Pride Cell,

00:28:35.847 --> 00:28:38.680
still don't allow it!

00:28:42.180 --> 00:28:43.847
I'm really...

00:28:45.843 --> 00:28:49.097
This is so heavy.

00:28:49.097 --> 00:28:52.058
This wasn't necessary,

00:28:52.058 --> 00:28:53.263
but thanks, I'll enjoy it.

00:28:53.263 --> 00:28:54.310
Okay.

00:28:54.310 --> 00:28:57.070
See you on meeting day.

00:29:00.805 --> 00:29:02.135
Give him a ride, at least.

00:29:02.135 --> 00:29:04.847
That much, I, Pride Cell, allow.

00:29:04.847 --> 00:29:07.055
Where are you going?

00:29:09.700 --> 00:29:11.869
Headed to the publisher.

00:29:11.869 --> 00:29:14.180
- Let me drop you off.
- No, I'm fine.

00:29:14.180 --> 00:29:15.222
Get in.

00:29:15.222 --> 00:29:19.097
I'm heading to the publisher to see the editor.

00:29:19.888 --> 00:29:21.888
Come on, get in.

00:29:21.888 --> 00:29:23.939
Okay.

00:29:34.850 --> 00:29:36.560
Let's head out.

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:38.486
Sure.

00:29:43.347 --> 00:29:46.805
She shouldn't have offered him a ride.

00:29:49.263 --> 00:29:51.909
- How come?
- I'm so anxious.

00:29:51.909 --> 00:29:54.578
The publisher's like 20 minutes away.

00:29:54.578 --> 00:29:57.081
What are they supposed to talk about?

00:29:57.081 --> 00:29:59.097
PD Shin's not gonna talk.

00:29:59.097 --> 00:30:00.347
What then?

00:30:00.347 --> 00:30:03.921
They're going the same way.
She can't bail on him.

00:30:03.921 --> 00:30:07.390
She could die from how awkward this is.

00:30:09.175 --> 00:30:10.719
This isn't going to work.

00:30:10.719 --> 00:30:13.771
- Reaction No. 1!
- Yes!

00:30:24.316 --> 00:30:26.867
Hey, Reaction No. 1, what're you doing?

00:30:27.569 --> 00:30:29.863
Looking through the chat list.

00:30:29.863 --> 00:30:32.373
Hold on a second.

00:30:34.472 --> 00:30:36.684
It's already silent.

00:30:36.684 --> 00:30:39.013
What do they do?

00:30:39.013 --> 00:30:40.415
Let's play music.

00:30:40.415 --> 00:30:42.716
That way they can stop talking.

00:30:51.760 --> 00:30:55.930
Any music you're into?

00:30:55.930 --> 00:30:58.308
Not really, no.

00:30:58.308 --> 00:31:00.347
Oh, okay.

00:31:00.347 --> 00:31:03.263
Then...

00:31:03.263 --> 00:31:04.513
Hey, there's a car!

00:31:04.513 --> 00:31:06.307
Oh my!

00:31:08.388 --> 00:31:09.944
What's wrong with that car?

00:31:09.944 --> 00:31:11.430
Why's he coming in the exit?

00:31:11.430 --> 00:31:13.680
What's up with him?

00:31:14.616 --> 00:31:17.327
Writer Kim, you came in the wrong way.

00:31:17.327 --> 00:31:19.079
What?

00:31:19.079 --> 00:31:20.838
Look over there.

00:31:21.430 --> 00:31:22.491
What?

00:31:22.491 --> 00:31:25.311
- Oh, what do I do?
- Hey, what're you doing?

00:31:30.548 --> 00:31:32.263
Oh no, what now?

00:31:32.263 --> 00:31:34.305
- No...
- You should back up first.

00:31:34.305 --> 00:31:35.345
Back it up.

00:31:35.345 --> 00:31:37.209
A bit further back should do it.

00:31:37.209 --> 00:31:38.765
Right, reverse.

00:31:38.765 --> 00:31:41.893
Reverse...

00:31:41.893 --> 00:31:44.069
- Let me help you.
- Sure.

00:31:48.321 --> 00:31:49.388
Stop!

00:31:49.388 --> 00:31:50.763
Watch the right side!

00:31:50.763 --> 00:31:52.737
Try going forward first.

00:31:52.737 --> 00:31:55.581
- And then reverse.
- Got it.

00:31:58.743 --> 00:32:01.222
Wheel to the right.

00:32:01.222 --> 00:32:02.705
Stop there.

00:32:02.705 --> 00:32:04.757
Go ahead and reverse now.

00:32:06.472 --> 00:32:09.097
- Just keep backing up.
- Got it.

00:32:09.097 --> 00:32:11.339
Slowly crank the wheel to the right.

00:32:11.339 --> 00:32:13.390
To the right?

00:32:15.051 --> 00:32:17.056
Stop there!

00:32:20.581 --> 00:32:23.097
How about I take over?

00:32:23.097 --> 00:32:25.730
Yeah, that sounds good.

00:32:30.011 --> 00:32:31.055
Writer Kim?

00:32:31.055 --> 00:32:33.097
Step out, please.

00:32:35.731 --> 00:32:38.832
I can't really get out though...

00:32:39.430 --> 00:32:42.004
- Come out this way.
- Okay.

00:32:46.138 --> 00:32:47.638
Hold on.

00:32:47.638 --> 00:32:49.648
Thank you.

00:32:52.380 --> 00:32:54.310
Get in.

00:33:40.512 --> 00:33:43.972
PD Shin's a good driver.

00:33:43.972 --> 00:33:47.563
What a relief.

00:33:58.736 --> 00:34:01.281
- What're you doing?
- I'm sorry.

00:34:01.281 --> 00:34:03.207
I'm sorry.

00:34:06.703 --> 00:34:09.630
Gosh, he scared me.

00:34:11.124 --> 00:34:13.293
Let's grab a cab.

00:34:13.293 --> 00:34:15.086
I'll handle the parking.

00:34:15.086 --> 00:34:16.671
Yeah, that works.

00:34:16.671 --> 00:34:18.798
I got so startled too...

00:34:18.798 --> 00:34:20.871
Okay.

00:34:36.722 --> 00:34:39.694
I was really on edge.

00:34:39.694 --> 00:34:44.073
What would she do without PD Shin?

00:34:44.073 --> 00:34:46.847
Take this as a rush delivery.

00:34:46.847 --> 00:34:47.972
Got it.

00:34:57.587 --> 00:35:00.388
Hey, where to this time?

00:35:02.847 --> 00:35:05.011
It's a rush job.

00:35:05.011 --> 00:35:06.471
Not happening!

00:35:06.471 --> 00:35:08.139
My pride still won't allow...

00:35:08.139 --> 00:35:09.640
You're still at it?

00:35:09.640 --> 00:35:13.013
It's only polite to compliment him.

00:35:13.013 --> 00:35:16.230
Don't let pride wreck Yumi's manners!

00:35:16.230 --> 00:35:18.138
Manners Cell, good job.

00:35:18.138 --> 00:35:20.401
Hurry, deliver it! Go, go!

00:35:20.401 --> 00:35:22.362
Okay!

00:35:22.362 --> 00:35:25.581
Go!

00:35:34.972 --> 00:35:37.388
I'll call a taxi.

00:35:37.388 --> 00:35:39.763
Thank you so much.

00:35:40.972 --> 00:35:43.722
You drive really well.

00:35:43.722 --> 00:35:45.051
It's nothing.

00:35:45.051 --> 00:35:46.379
No, really.

00:35:46.379 --> 00:35:49.972
What if you hadn't been there?

00:35:49.972 --> 00:35:52.180
That was such a mess.

00:35:52.180 --> 00:35:56.020
How long have you been driving?

00:35:56.020 --> 00:35:57.869
Well...

00:35:57.869 --> 00:36:01.082
About six months since I started again.

00:36:01.082 --> 00:36:02.652
Six months?

00:36:02.652 --> 00:36:04.328
Yes.

00:36:15.097 --> 00:36:16.874
- Who's there?
- Who is it?

00:36:16.874 --> 00:36:19.763
Hi, I'm from Soon Rok's village.

00:36:19.763 --> 00:36:22.263
I've got a delivery.

00:36:26.847 --> 00:36:29.597
Soon Rok sent a delivery too.

00:36:29.597 --> 00:36:31.805
- What is it?
- I hope it's nice.

00:36:31.805 --> 00:36:34.888
This could help them get closer.

00:36:36.143 --> 00:36:37.436
What's this?

00:36:37.436 --> 00:36:39.813
- Not every delivery is a compliment.
- What is that?

00:36:39.813 --> 00:36:41.356
It's totally blank.

00:36:41.356 --> 00:36:42.888
Why's the paper empty?

00:36:42.888 --> 00:36:44.388
Wait a second.

00:36:44.388 --> 00:36:47.480
It's not empty.

00:36:49.097 --> 00:36:52.638
Wait, there's a secret message.

00:36:52.638 --> 00:36:54.725
A secret code?

00:36:57.789 --> 00:37:00.250
Look, it's showing up!

00:37:00.250 --> 00:37:03.170
- "Quit"
- "Quit"

00:37:03.170 --> 00:37:05.630
- "driving"
- "driving"

00:37:05.630 --> 00:37:07.299
- "already."
- "already."

00:37:07.299 --> 00:37:10.434
Some deliveries are silent mockery.

00:37:12.803 --> 00:37:15.236
[Quit driving already]

00:37:17.934 --> 00:37:21.612
- Quit driving already.
- Quit driving already.

00:37:25.817 --> 00:37:27.474
Whoever gets this delivery

00:37:27.474 --> 00:37:30.097
- feels upset for no reason.
- That jerk...

00:37:30.097 --> 00:37:33.180
They feel completely insulted.

00:37:42.167 --> 00:37:44.263
That was fast.

00:37:44.263 --> 00:37:46.763
Going up.

00:37:49.341 --> 00:37:51.684
The doors are closing.

00:37:52.302 --> 00:37:54.061
Writer Kim?

00:38:03.263 --> 00:38:05.844
[Episode 6: Time for a Change]

00:38:08.902 --> 00:38:11.238
Hey, Fishing Cell.

00:38:11.238 --> 00:38:14.031
- Yeah?
- Got another angry snapper today?

00:38:14.031 --> 00:38:17.326
If every day were like this, I'd be set.

00:38:17.326 --> 00:38:21.372
PD Shin deserves a thank-you gift.

00:38:21.372 --> 00:38:22.638
Rational Cell.

00:38:22.638 --> 00:38:24.834
I'm freaking out again.

00:38:24.834 --> 00:38:26.961
Seriously, what's wrong now?

00:38:26.961 --> 00:38:28.462
I'm so nervous.

00:38:28.462 --> 00:38:32.466
She's got Busan tomorrow, needs sleep.

00:38:32.466 --> 00:38:36.686
What if she misses the train?

00:38:39.140 --> 00:38:41.441
Really.

00:38:45.688 --> 00:38:47.989
Seriously.

00:38:49.955 --> 00:38:54.472
She's still wide awake.

00:38:54.472 --> 00:38:57.199
She'd sleep if you stopped panicking.

00:38:57.199 --> 00:38:59.160
So hungry!

00:38:59.160 --> 00:39:00.619
Let's eat something!

00:39:00.619 --> 00:39:02.538
Let's have a midnight snack!

00:39:02.538 --> 00:39:05.006
What's wrong with you?

00:39:07.084 --> 00:39:09.337
I'm starving.

00:39:09.337 --> 00:39:12.013
I'm hungry.

00:39:21.265 --> 00:39:25.952
Yumi, let's eat the 3-star dessert.

00:39:25.952 --> 00:39:27.521
Come on, let's eat it.

00:39:27.521 --> 00:39:31.283
I've been craving it for a while.

00:39:35.930 --> 00:39:37.680
Forget it, I won't touch it.

00:39:37.680 --> 00:39:40.180
I'd rather eat my bungeoppang.

00:39:53.847 --> 00:39:56.388
Because of that guy, I keep snacking.

00:39:56.388 --> 00:39:58.597
My blood sugar's dropping.

00:40:11.680 --> 00:40:15.660
How long have you been driving?

00:40:18.155 --> 00:40:20.741
Come on, I'm still learning.

00:40:20.741 --> 00:40:24.411
He reversed once and looked at me like that?

00:40:24.411 --> 00:40:27.347
Unbelievable.

00:40:27.347 --> 00:40:29.332
[Quit driving already]

00:40:29.332 --> 00:40:32.919
Told you not to send that package.

00:40:32.919 --> 00:40:35.504
You sent it on your own, your fault!

00:40:35.504 --> 00:40:39.133
I didn't know he had zero manners.

00:40:39.133 --> 00:40:42.345
I want dessert!

00:40:42.345 --> 00:40:44.388
Let's eat dessert!

00:40:44.388 --> 00:40:47.010
- Hey! Have some pride, please!
- Dessert!

00:40:47.010 --> 00:40:51.813
- You'd eat his charity dessert now?
- I want dessert!

00:40:52.521 --> 00:40:56.472
But I want it!

00:40:56.472 --> 00:41:00.196
Dessert!

00:41:00.196 --> 00:41:02.055
Guys, aren't you going to bed?

00:41:02.055 --> 00:41:04.461
- Dessert!
- When am I supposed to work?

00:41:04.461 --> 00:41:05.493
Hey.

00:41:05.493 --> 00:41:07.870
We hired PD Shin to help me write.

00:41:07.870 --> 00:41:09.538
Not to piss me off every day!

00:41:09.538 --> 00:41:13.042
Can't get a moment of peace here!

00:41:13.042 --> 00:41:14.252
Calm down.

00:41:14.252 --> 00:41:17.012
She'll adjust to him eventually.

00:41:17.964 --> 00:41:20.341
No, swap him out.

00:41:20.341 --> 00:41:22.180
Swap him out?

00:41:22.180 --> 00:41:25.346
Tell Editor An we want a new PD.

00:41:25.346 --> 00:41:29.600
If he's in the way, he must be removed.

00:41:29.600 --> 00:41:31.269
Should I

00:41:31.269 --> 00:41:33.396
just ask for a new PD?

00:41:33.396 --> 00:41:35.773
You see Editor An in Busan tomorrow.

00:41:35.773 --> 00:41:39.527
No PD Shin around. It's the perfect time.

00:41:39.527 --> 00:41:42.238
Didn't you say his feedback was useful?

00:41:42.238 --> 00:41:44.532
If I can't write just to get his notes,

00:41:44.532 --> 00:41:46.075
I'd rather skip it completely.

00:41:46.075 --> 00:41:48.411
That might really be the better choice.

00:41:48.411 --> 00:41:50.413
Shin Soon Rok, the pain in the neck,

00:41:50.413 --> 00:41:52.123
isn't going to change anytime soon.

00:41:52.123 --> 00:41:53.332
Exactly my point.

00:41:53.332 --> 00:41:55.710
All right, let's say she meets him.

00:41:55.710 --> 00:41:57.503
Then what does she tell him?

00:41:57.503 --> 00:41:59.171
So...

00:41:59.171 --> 00:42:03.884
You're saying kick PD Shin out?

00:42:03.884 --> 00:42:05.886
Yeah.

00:42:05.886 --> 00:42:08.055
Sure, understood.

00:42:08.055 --> 00:42:10.933
If he's no help to your work, he's out.

00:42:10.933 --> 00:42:12.101
But...

00:42:12.101 --> 00:42:14.228
could you tell me

00:42:14.228 --> 00:42:16.430
what specifically bothered you?

00:42:16.430 --> 00:42:19.680
Oh, well...

00:42:20.276 --> 00:42:23.870
He called Maltese dogs stupid.

00:42:24.488 --> 00:42:27.541
Because he called Maltese dogs stupid?

00:42:28.868 --> 00:42:30.536
Is that really a reason to replace him?

00:42:30.536 --> 00:42:33.289
That sounds kind of petty.

00:42:33.289 --> 00:42:36.542
He took all eight Strawberry Cream

00:42:36.542 --> 00:42:39.754
Custard Bungeoppang I love, and it upset me...

00:42:39.754 --> 00:42:43.007
Over eight Strawberry Cream Bungeoppang?

00:42:43.007 --> 00:42:45.468
Gosh, that's pretty petty too.

00:42:45.468 --> 00:42:47.853
Bungeoppang? Really?

00:42:48.805 --> 00:42:51.098
We rode the bus together,

00:42:51.098 --> 00:42:54.810
and he just put his earphones on alone.

00:42:54.810 --> 00:42:56.103
Over earphones?

00:42:56.103 --> 00:42:59.722
Gosh, that's super petty!

00:42:59.722 --> 00:43:01.923
He laughed at me

00:43:01.923 --> 00:43:03.861
for being a bad driver.

00:43:03.861 --> 00:43:06.997
He was definitely laughing at me.

00:43:07.805 --> 00:43:10.242
His face,

00:43:10.242 --> 00:43:12.203
it was exactly like this!

00:43:12.203 --> 00:43:13.996
No way!

00:43:13.996 --> 00:43:18.341
This is way too petty!

00:43:21.138 --> 00:43:23.756
No.

00:43:23.756 --> 00:43:26.467
There's no real reason to replace him.

00:43:26.467 --> 00:43:28.768
No justification.

00:43:29.597 --> 00:43:32.390
These reasons are just lame.

00:43:32.390 --> 00:43:35.150
I'll only embarrass myself.

00:43:36.805 --> 00:43:38.972
But

00:43:38.972 --> 00:43:41.597
the lame reasons make me even madder.

00:43:44.276 --> 00:43:46.870
Why am I so annoyed?

00:43:48.555 --> 00:43:51.992
Come on, let's calm down.

00:43:51.992 --> 00:43:54.787
A trip to Busan will clear your mind,

00:43:54.787 --> 00:43:57.847
and you may see it differently.

00:43:57.847 --> 00:44:00.680
Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.

00:44:00.680 --> 00:44:05.423
- Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.
- Shin Soon Rok isn't worth it.

00:44:05.423 --> 00:44:07.142
Yeah, let's do that.

00:44:07.142 --> 00:44:09.430
I'll decide when I get back.

00:44:09.430 --> 00:44:11.937
Why am I even stressing over him?

00:44:49.263 --> 00:44:51.290
9 a.m.

00:44:51.290 --> 00:44:54.062
I'm here a bit early.

00:44:55.472 --> 00:44:59.472
Hi PD Jang, I made it.

00:45:05.398 --> 00:45:07.733
Rational Cell,

00:45:07.733 --> 00:45:10.194
something's bugging me.

00:45:10.194 --> 00:45:11.988
What are you worried about now?

00:45:11.988 --> 00:45:13.097
You know,

00:45:13.097 --> 00:45:15.847
what if PD Jang suddenly can't make it

00:45:15.847 --> 00:45:20.180
and PD Shin shows up instead?

00:45:21.055 --> 00:45:24.000
- What would she do then?
- Hey!

00:45:24.000 --> 00:45:26.252
Quit saying horrible stuff like that!

00:45:26.252 --> 00:45:30.138
Take the train to Busan with that guy?

00:45:30.138 --> 00:45:32.216
For that many hours?

00:45:32.216 --> 00:45:35.472
Yumi seriously couldn't breathe.

00:45:35.472 --> 00:45:39.722
She could die!

00:45:50.860 --> 00:45:53.571
- Hi, PD Jang.
- Writer Kim!

00:45:53.571 --> 00:45:54.697
Where are you?

00:45:54.697 --> 00:45:56.073
What do I do?

00:45:56.073 --> 00:45:57.658
Something happened.

00:45:57.658 --> 00:45:59.972
My younger sister's having early labor,

00:45:59.972 --> 00:46:01.537
and nobody's home right now.

00:46:01.537 --> 00:46:03.497
I need to go with her.

00:46:03.497 --> 00:46:05.207
Oh my, that's terrible.

00:46:05.207 --> 00:46:08.210
So I asked PD Shin to go instead.

00:46:08.210 --> 00:46:09.638
PD Shin?

00:46:09.638 --> 00:46:11.472
I knew it!

00:46:11.472 --> 00:46:14.759
I said I was worried!

00:46:14.759 --> 00:46:18.137
He just left, but he may run a little late.

00:46:18.137 --> 00:46:20.056
Wait,

00:46:20.056 --> 00:46:24.583
am I traveling with PD Shin?

00:46:24.583 --> 00:46:26.472
Yes, why don't you get on first?

00:46:26.472 --> 00:46:30.358
He can take the next train if he's late.

00:46:30.358 --> 00:46:32.485
Oh, sure.

00:46:32.485 --> 00:46:34.661
Yes, understood.

00:46:39.222 --> 00:46:41.847
Come on, be late, please be late.

00:46:42.787 --> 00:46:45.088
Don't come!

00:47:13.192 --> 00:47:15.319
Good morning, passengers.

00:47:15.319 --> 00:47:18.864
This is the express train to Busan Station.

00:47:18.864 --> 00:47:21.784
Our crew will do everything we can

00:47:21.784 --> 00:47:23.660
to make your ride pleasant.

00:47:23.660 --> 00:47:27.205
No way I can ride with Shin Soon Rok.

00:47:27.205 --> 00:47:29.374
How do I put up with that awkwardness?

00:47:29.374 --> 00:47:32.301
Even seeing his face bugs me.

00:47:35.297 --> 00:47:38.891
Come on, be late. It's better that way.

00:47:40.222 --> 00:47:41.753
[Busan]

00:47:49.728 --> 00:47:51.654
Train's moving.

00:48:03.533 --> 00:48:07.962
- Hurray! We're saved!
- Hurray!

00:48:12.751 --> 00:48:16.504
Is this really something to celebrate?

00:48:16.504 --> 00:48:18.514
We're supposed to be a team...

00:48:19.257 --> 00:48:21.851
Oh, I don't care.

00:48:30.722 --> 00:48:32.680
Writer Kim.

00:48:53.958 --> 00:48:57.303
I barely made the train.

00:48:59.055 --> 00:49:00.638
You heard about it, right?

00:49:00.638 --> 00:49:03.637
I'm going with you instead.

00:49:03.637 --> 00:49:05.303
Oh, right.

00:49:05.303 --> 00:49:07.938
Oh, sure.

00:49:08.763 --> 00:49:11.101
So, you made it on?

00:49:11.101 --> 00:49:12.602
Yeah,

00:49:12.602 --> 00:49:14.771
I had to run.

00:49:14.771 --> 00:49:17.513
Oh, you had to run.

00:49:17.513 --> 00:49:21.513
Oh, good thing we're going together.

00:49:22.986 --> 00:49:25.072
You usually wear glasses, right?

00:49:25.072 --> 00:49:27.866
Yeah, I left them behind.

00:49:27.866 --> 00:49:30.126
I see.

00:49:30.994 --> 00:49:33.372
Without glasses, he seems like someone else.

00:49:33.372 --> 00:49:35.934
Yeah, and his hair's down in front.

00:49:37.584 --> 00:49:39.795
Everyone, no time for gossip.

00:49:39.795 --> 00:49:41.213
Red alert!

00:49:41.213 --> 00:49:43.763
Okay, everyone get ready.

00:49:43.763 --> 00:49:45.050
Especially you, Reaction No. 1!

00:49:45.050 --> 00:49:47.177
- Stay sharp.
- Got it!

00:49:47.177 --> 00:49:49.680
Emotion Cell, Pride Cell, stay calm.

00:49:49.680 --> 00:49:51.682
You've got Cursing Cell locked up, right?

00:49:51.682 --> 00:49:53.350
Don't let her say a word.

00:49:53.350 --> 00:49:57.020
Manners Cell,
stay chill if he puts earphones on.

00:49:57.020 --> 00:49:58.176
- Hungry Cell!
- Yeah?

00:49:58.176 --> 00:50:01.198
Be ready if he eats snacks by himself.

00:50:02.693 --> 00:50:04.888
It's two and a half hours to Busan.

00:50:05.638 --> 00:50:07.906
We just need to hold on for that long.

00:50:07.906 --> 00:50:08.949
When we're in Busan,

00:50:08.949 --> 00:50:11.743
the super friendly Editor An is waiting.

00:50:11.743 --> 00:50:14.170
- We got this!
- Right!

00:50:14.830 --> 00:50:18.383
Great, going alone would've been dull.

00:50:18.383 --> 00:50:19.418
Please sit down.

00:50:19.418 --> 00:50:22.963
No, my seat is over there.

00:50:22.963 --> 00:50:24.965
Oh, is that so?

00:50:24.965 --> 00:50:27.092
They didn't have a seat next to yours.

00:50:27.092 --> 00:50:29.143
Got it.

00:50:29.970 --> 00:50:34.391
- He's sitting somewhere else!
- He's not sitting with us!

00:50:34.391 --> 00:50:36.351
See you when we arrive.

00:50:36.351 --> 00:50:38.101
Sure.

00:50:51.116 --> 00:50:53.334
Oh, thank goodness.

00:50:58.999 --> 00:51:00.959
All right, emergency's over.

00:51:00.959 --> 00:51:04.379
Get some rest until we reach Busan.

00:51:04.379 --> 00:51:05.751
Hold on.

00:51:05.751 --> 00:51:07.722
This seems weird.

00:51:07.722 --> 00:51:11.705
You think he sat apart on purpose?

00:51:11.705 --> 00:51:13.638
Because he didn't want to sit with Yumi.

00:51:13.638 --> 00:51:16.055
- What?
- What?

00:51:19.263 --> 00:51:22.013
Look how many empty seats there are.

00:51:22.013 --> 00:51:24.263
Doesn't that feel weird?

00:51:26.722 --> 00:51:28.638
So many empty seats around,

00:51:28.638 --> 00:51:31.930
he chose the farthest seat?

00:51:33.430 --> 00:51:36.036
He actually sat far away on purpose?

00:51:36.036 --> 00:51:39.122
If that's the case, I'm not letting it slide.

00:51:39.122 --> 00:51:42.125
No way, it can't be.

00:51:42.125 --> 00:51:45.462
If that's real, it's outrageous.

00:51:45.462 --> 00:51:48.723
I'm the one holding back here!

00:51:57.464 --> 00:51:58.763
Hello?

00:51:58.763 --> 00:52:00.936
Hey, Writer Kim, traveling okay?

00:52:00.936 --> 00:52:02.555
Yes, I boarded a little bit ago.

00:52:02.555 --> 00:52:04.772
I heard something came up for PD Jang.

00:52:04.772 --> 00:52:07.566
Right, so I'm going with PD Shin.

00:52:07.566 --> 00:52:08.818
Right, I was told.

00:52:08.818 --> 00:52:11.529
I've got work, I'll come down later.

00:52:11.529 --> 00:52:13.739
Let's grab dinner tonight.

00:52:13.739 --> 00:52:16.117
Sounds good.

00:52:16.117 --> 00:52:17.952
Well...

00:52:17.952 --> 00:52:20.121
The thing is,

00:52:20.121 --> 00:52:22.915
so, about PD Shin.

00:52:22.915 --> 00:52:24.208
Okay.

00:52:24.208 --> 00:52:26.836
Is he with you? I can call you back.

00:52:26.836 --> 00:52:31.139
No, our seats are separate, he's far away.

00:52:32.216 --> 00:52:35.560
So regarding PD Shin...

00:52:36.721 --> 00:52:38.055
What now?

00:52:38.055 --> 00:52:39.932
Why's he dragging it out like this?

00:52:39.932 --> 00:52:43.102
I'm already nervous.

00:52:43.102 --> 00:52:46.522
It's only been a few days since he joined,

00:52:46.522 --> 00:52:48.566
so I just wanted to check,

00:52:48.566 --> 00:52:52.327
is it all right if we reassign him?

00:52:54.488 --> 00:52:57.805
Reassign? So you're...

00:52:57.805 --> 00:53:01.347
swapping the PD out?

00:53:04.722 --> 00:53:09.013
Right, if you don't mind, can we swap him?

00:53:15.676 --> 00:53:17.404
Make some noise!

00:53:19.263 --> 00:53:22.683
Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!

00:53:22.683 --> 00:53:26.222
- Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!
- Shin Soon Rok's out, oh yeah!

00:53:26.222 --> 00:53:28.722
Oh, sure,

00:53:29.732 --> 00:53:31.650
I'm fine

00:53:31.650 --> 00:53:32.902
with that.

00:53:32.902 --> 00:53:34.862
Really? You don't mind?

00:53:34.862 --> 00:53:36.619
It is a bit of a shame,

00:53:36.619 --> 00:53:37.680
but...

00:53:37.680 --> 00:53:40.868
we just started working together,

00:53:40.868 --> 00:53:43.388
so it won't really set things back.

00:53:43.388 --> 00:53:45.013
Oh, that's a relief.

00:53:45.013 --> 00:53:46.916
Thanks for understanding.

00:53:46.916 --> 00:53:48.013
No problem.

00:53:48.013 --> 00:53:51.180
I'll look for another solid PD for you.

00:53:51.180 --> 00:53:53.680
All right, see you there.

00:53:53.680 --> 00:53:56.847
Yes, see you later.

00:54:01.137 --> 00:54:04.724
Is it really working out this easily?

00:54:04.724 --> 00:54:06.475
Perfect timing.

00:54:06.475 --> 00:54:08.895
He's out without her saying anything petty.

00:54:08.895 --> 00:54:10.555
Good thing she held back.

00:54:10.555 --> 00:54:12.190
Patience really does pay off.

00:54:12.190 --> 00:54:16.100
Finally, I can focus on writing.

00:54:18.237 --> 00:54:19.871
Wait.

00:54:20.573 --> 00:54:24.793
So this trip is my last one with him?

00:54:26.162 --> 00:54:27.972
Oh my.

00:54:27.972 --> 00:54:30.868
Now I'm actually enjoying this ride.

00:54:47.600 --> 00:54:49.818
Please insert your card.

00:55:02.323 --> 00:55:04.666
Why not, I'm in a good mood.

00:55:19.340 --> 00:55:20.680
Here, drink this while you work.

00:55:20.680 --> 00:55:23.232
Oh, thank you.

00:55:28.182 --> 00:55:31.610
I just talked to Editor An.

00:55:33.396 --> 00:55:36.232
We just started, and already it's goodbye.

00:55:36.232 --> 00:55:37.275
Right?

00:55:37.275 --> 00:55:39.026
Guess we need a farewell party.

00:55:39.026 --> 00:55:40.695
I'll miss working with you.

00:55:40.695 --> 00:55:41.888
I'm sorry.

00:55:41.888 --> 00:55:43.656
You've got nothing to be sorry for...

00:55:43.656 --> 00:55:46.875
Thank you for understanding.

00:55:52.638 --> 00:55:55.647
Go ahead and answer it.

00:55:57.795 --> 00:55:59.721
Hello?

00:56:00.881 --> 00:56:03.433
Yeah, I just left.

00:56:04.805 --> 00:56:06.554
Something feels off.

00:56:06.554 --> 00:56:08.139
Totally off.

00:56:08.139 --> 00:56:10.357
Let's check it out.

00:56:21.652 --> 00:56:22.820
Hi, Writer Kim.

00:56:22.820 --> 00:56:24.405
Hi, Editor An.

00:56:24.405 --> 00:56:26.657
I've got a question.

00:56:26.657 --> 00:56:29.388
Why are you swapping him all of a sudden?

00:56:29.388 --> 00:56:30.453
Sorry?

00:56:30.453 --> 00:56:33.138
Did PD Shin ask for it, by any chance...

00:56:33.138 --> 00:56:37.543
Oh, he already told you?

00:56:37.543 --> 00:56:39.847
Juggling it with his other work was hard,

00:56:39.847 --> 00:56:43.138
so he wants to focus on just one project.

00:56:45.968 --> 00:56:49.020
Seems it was overwhelming him.

00:56:50.806 --> 00:56:52.433
What the heck?

00:56:52.433 --> 00:56:57.112
So he's the one who wanted out?

00:56:58.722 --> 00:57:01.817
Yumi was holding back this whole time.

00:57:01.817 --> 00:57:04.638
Now he's the one leaving?

00:57:04.638 --> 00:57:06.614
If anyone's dumping anyone, it's Yumi!

00:57:06.614 --> 00:57:10.041
Who's he to drop Yumi?

00:57:30.263 --> 00:57:32.906
This is killing me!

00:57:33.557 --> 00:57:35.684
He's leaving anyway.

00:57:35.684 --> 00:57:39.013
He's leaving even if you hold back. Let it out!

00:57:39.013 --> 00:57:42.347
You're old enough to speak up, Kim Yumi!

00:57:52.555 --> 00:57:54.930
Let me sit beside you for a moment.

00:57:58.498 --> 00:58:00.847
We need to talk.

00:58:00.847 --> 00:58:03.545
- Pardon?
- You don't like working with me?

00:58:03.545 --> 00:58:05.221
What is it exactly?

00:58:10.719 --> 00:58:12.929
Could you be specific?

00:58:12.929 --> 00:58:15.314
I want an answer.

00:58:55.407 --> 00:58:57.972
Wait, lightning? Out of a clear blue sky?

00:58:57.972 --> 00:59:00.222
- Hey! What the...
- Didn't he miss it intentionally?

00:59:00.222 --> 00:59:02.805
Come on, why?

00:59:02.805 --> 00:59:04.314
We're in trouble.

00:59:04.314 --> 00:59:08.193
The whole village is in chaos!

00:59:08.193 --> 00:59:10.028
Did Love Cell wake up?

00:59:10.028 --> 00:59:11.446
What for?

00:59:11.446 --> 00:59:13.562
- Thump, thump.
- Writer Kim.

00:59:13.562 --> 00:59:15.825
- Thump, thump.
- Thump, thump.

00:59:15.825 --> 00:59:18.638
Thump, thump.

00:59:18.638 --> 00:59:21.859
Why's her heart pounding out of nowhere?